{
  "text": "Just before the end of the salivarium cavity, paired salivary ducts enter into its lateral corners [CITATION_1] . Both salivary ducts are enclosed in a sheet of tissue (TSD in Fig. 2C ,E,F,M,N, dark purple) that probably flexibly fastens the salivary ducts to the lateral corners of the salivarium.",
